snippet: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s image of invincibility has taken a knock, but his political future seems assured because he has no obvious rival for the premiership, Israeli analysts said.
abstract: Israeli analysts say that Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s image of invincibility has taken a knock after the breakup of the large and broad coalition that had given him almost unprecedented power; his political future, however, seems assured, as he has no obvious rival.
lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s image of invincibility has taken a knock, but his political future seems assured because he has no obvious rival for the premiership, Israeli analysts said.

headline.seo: Damage Limited for Netanhayu in Coalition’s Breakup
headline.main: Though Bruised, Netanyahu Is Seen as Secure in Post After Coalition’s Demise
headline.print_headline: Though Bruised, Netanyahu Is Seen as Secure in Post After Coalition’s Demise
